# Console design

Full guide: `docs/console-design.md`. Read it when planning or building console UI.

## Navigation

- **Top bar:** org name + chevron menu (Home · Apps · Team) · search · account. No inline Home/Apps/Team links.
- **Search:** icon on mobile, full bar on `md+`. Same ⌘K dialog everywhere.
- **Breadcrumbs:** truncate and collapse with `…` dropdown. Never push search or profile off-screen (`shrink-0` on the right cluster).

## Page patterns (pick one)

| Pattern | When | Use |
|---------|------|-----|
| Hub | Overview / landing | Metric cards, next steps — `HomeView` |
| List | Index of records | `ListPageHeader` + `DataTable` |
| List tabs | Two related lists | `ResourceTabs` only (e.g. Members \| Invites) |
| **Workspace** | Multi-section entity | Header block + **`SectionSidebar`** + `<Outlet />` |
| Detail | Single view | `EntityDetailLayout` without tabs |

**Do not** use horizontal `PageTabBar` / line tabs for entity sections. Use `SectionSidebar` (same as Apps and Profile).

## Reuse these

- `SectionSidebar` — app sections, profile, any future multi-section module
- `AppWorkspaceLayout` — app-scoped pages
- `DataTable` — toolbar and pagination **inside** the card
- shadcn primitives from `components/ui/` — never hand-roll buttons, dialogs, tables

## Copy

- One question per screen; plain language; **no em-dashes** in UI strings.
- Bold numbers on metrics; short status tokens (`Off`, `On`), not sentences.

## Before shipping

Check ~390px and ~1024px: header controls visible, breadcrumbs collapse, sidebar scrolls horizontally on mobile.
